		{
			"id": 132,
			"type": "MarkdownNote",
			"pos": [-520, 480],
			"size": [280, 280],
			"flags": {},
			"order": 4,
			"mode": 0,
			"inputs": [],
			"outputs": [],
			"title": "General use",
			"properties": {},
			"widgets_values": [
				"Connect model and CLIP from a checkpoint loader, then click ➕ Add LoRA to add rows.\n\n## Modes\n\n**Without model/clip:** the node only builds a LORA_STACK — feed the stack output to a downstream loader that has model/clip connected. This lets you define LoRAs once and apply them to several models.\n\n**With model/clip:** the node verifies each LoRA to only enables the ones compatible with the model. The model and clip output can be used directly.\n\n## Chain\n\nYou can chain the Mega Lora Loaders in both modes."
			],
			"color": "#232",
			"bgcolor": "#353"
		},
